<Author>Bevla
<Content>Nice hotel, bad staff This hotel is lovely and situated in perfect distance of AlexanderPlatz and there is a very handy U-Bahn just outside the front door. The rooms are lovely, comfortable and clean not huge but big enough, not all rooms have a bath so if you want one you should ask but the bathroom itself is spacious and well lit with lots of mirrors.The staff however are terribly rude and unhelpful. When we checked in we weren't told simple things such as check out time, breakfast timings (especcially as we went over a bank holiday as breakfast time is different to normal). We weren't told about being able to use the bar at the sister hotel over the road and we weren't told to bring our guest passes with us otherwise they grumble at you when you ask for your key back after being out.When checking out we were told that the luggage store was full and they had no where to store our bags, although when we pressed the point they told us we could use the luggage store over the road, why were we not automatically given that option? Also we asked reception to book us a cab to the airport although when we got back to our hotel after being out for the morning we were told someone else had taken our car and she had failed to book us another one!!! We were there at the time we had requested the car for after all...Also the restaurant at the hotel, whilst supplying very yummy indian food (no onion bhajis though!) the service is terrible. We waited about an hour for our dinner, thankfully we weren't in a rush. After dinner we stayed in the restaurant for another couple of hours (as there is no bar in the hotel that is ever used) and we weren't asked once if we wanteed another drink. Everytime we beckoned the waiter over to ask for a drink he acted as if we were causing him great difficulty!and these are just some of the problems we encountered with the staff........!!To round it off I entirely recommend the location and the hotel rooms etc but not the service they provide, maybe try the hotel over the road??!!P.S if planning on going over new year be careful of everyone throwing fireworks in the street. Even out of their apartment windows! Scary! 
