<Author>skelghyl
<Content>So convenient If you are looking for a hotel 20m from an U-Bahn station but in a quiet part of former East Berlin then this is the place for you. The public transport in Berlin is second to none and this hotel is ideal to benefit from that. Rooms are comfortable and breakfast is plentiful setting you up for a day's sightseeing. When we were there between Christmas and New Year the bar was closed although it looked as if it had been closed for a while. You can use the bar facilites across the road in the sister hotel so not really an inconvenience. There was an Indian restaurant attached to the hotel which is fine if you can't be bothered to go out in the evening and we used it on arrival day for that reason. Good selection of restaurants in the Nicholai quarter which is a short walk away. But the location and the ease of use of the U-Bahn were the highlights for me. 
