<Author>BaselLisa
<Content>Will certainly go back to the Henriette! We booked the Hotel Henriette through the Berlin tourism office's site and were a bit dubious as to what kind of hotel we'd get for 67 euros. But it was only for one night, the other reviews on Trip Advisor were good, so we'd go for it. During the week, it seems to be much more expensive, so we came to the conclusion that it's primarily a business hotel that offers great weekend deals.What a lovely surprise! As others have pointed out, it's very well located, with a U-bahn station right outside, and easy walking distance to all the main sights of East Berlin. Our welcome was very friendly and professional. Our room was a decent size, not huge, spotlessly clean and well-equipped (hairdryer, fan, kettle, minibar etc). Because of its location, it was nice and quiet. The hotel itself was tastefully and elegantly decorated. When we were leaving, the receptionist was extremely helpful, even printing out timetables from the web to make sure we caught the right train to the airport. All in all, I'd highly recommend this hotel. I filled out their in-room questionnaire and was delighted to receive a follow-up message in the mail a few days later, inviting us to come and stay again. We certainly will. 
