<Author>hellij
<Content>Excellent location An excellent choice for a city break over Easter. Easy to get to from Shoenefeld airport as Ubahn station outside the hotel (change at Alexanderplatz) - open all hours, so late arrival not a problem. Upgraded to a room with 'tea-station' (although kettle only worked in our room), view of canal and interesting skyline. Good space and decor. Very good buffet breakfast - incredible range of teas!Location - superb. We chose to walk everywhere (partly to keep warm as it was cold with snow showers) but also because it is the best way to see the city. However, the transport system is cheap and effective. All main tourist locations within relatively easy walking distance.... and it is flat! Near to hotel- reasonable range of tourist restaurants nearby if you basically want to eat basic good German fayre, otherwise you may need to travel further afield (we didn't try the Indian restaurant attached to the hotel, but it was always busy and had reasonable menu).On our last day, cases kept in locked cupboard all day as we had late night plane to catch.Lovely, friendly staff. 
