<Author>Malroamer
<Content>A central Hotel although in the East Going to a new destination and knowing little about it makes booking an hotel difficult and can be worrying. As our son is living in Berlin he recommended the Dreag Henriette as it was the closest hotel to his apartment. He had not been inside but was told that the hotel was little known being in the East and off the beaten tourist map, but value for money.It is certainly value for money and compares well with UK hotel prices. The Hotel is not the Ritz but is comfortable, extremely clean, excellent breakfast, good and attentive service and staff speak enough English to understand and be understood. The only adverse comment I can make is that the coffee and tea supplies in the room were not replenished without asking and unfortunately there was not enough information about the room facilities and how to use them.Staff were frindly but not pushy, a good point.Bearing in mind the closeness to the U-bahn, twenty yards would be too far, the hotel suddenly becomes very accessible and convenient to all central points. Two stops to Alexanderplatz and Berlin becomes a smaller city.If we return to Berlin, the Henriette wold be first choice, but I think that it is becoming known and seems to enjoy good occupancy, which would mean early booking.Highly recommended! 
