<Author>pjeanne
<Content>Good value and well located but poor decoration The Derag Henriette is well located in East Berlin, near the main museums in a quiet (maybe too much?) area. However, it is just at a subway station which makes it a good point to discover the rest of the city (Berlin has one of the best public transport system I ever experienced). The staff is quite nice, but they did not anticipate our needs. Arriving late in the evening, our room was very hot due to an external temperature of 30C all day long and we realised that there was no fixed A/C unit available. However, the next day they came to fit in a mobile A/C unit which changed a lot the comfort. Otherwise, I found both the room and the bathroom a bit small for this category of hotel, but everything was new, very clean, soundproof and operational. Breakfast was good. The decoration is very much on the conservative side with a lot of very ugly and cheap looking paintings. But it still was a good value at 93 鈧?per night for 2 with breakfast 
