<Author>bbhmg
<Content>Ideal Situation I have stayed in Berlin many times but on this occasion needed an hotel which was Central...We use Easyjet to fly so this hotel came up on their website and after reading the description of the facilities, I decided to take the family for the Christmas Markets weekend..Our main disappointment was that the hotel did not help us with a smoking room with bath as requested via the Easyjet site and reception categorically told us that Easyjet had not passed on our requests...Yet the hotel were able to supply us with a third request from the same e-mail which was for adjoining rooms for my family.Otherwise it is an ideal jumping off point for all of Berlin since it is next to a U-Bahn which took us everywhere we wanted.The rooms were nice an warm and we slept well before going down for a great selection off the breakfast barAcross the road is the brother hotel (The Kurfurster) which had quality restaurant , fitness center and a bar which makes a change from the Henriette..........In summary, I can recommend the Henriette as a suitable hotel for a sightseeing visit to Berlin 
