<Author>Bequia1
<Content>A Nice Find I had wanted to find a nice, somewhat affordable hotel in Berlin for a recent trip, and wasn't at all sure where to go. All I knew was that I wanted to stay in East Berlin. I stumbled on the Hotel Henriette in a guide book, and it ended up being a very good choice. It's not as drop dead spectacular as some of the new modern chain hotels in Postdamerplatz, but it was certainly more intimate, and the staff took good care of me. Although the surrounding area may feel a bit out of the way, the hotel is actually in a very central location, on the Spee River virtually across from the Museum Island with its many museums and the Berliner Dom. The hotel itself is relatively small and modern (and as yet undiscovered by Americans), but it fits with the look and feel of the eastern half of the city. My room had built-in furniture (a bit like a ship) and was on the somewhat small side, like most European hotel rooms, but it was very comfortable and had tons of drawer space and all modern amenities. It also faced the river; a nice bonus (I suggest requesting a river view). The hotel has a nice restaurant and bar, and offers an excellent free breakfast. The staff were courteous and helpful.I would recommend the Hotel Henriette to anyone looking for a bit of (affordable) calm in the midst of this sprawling, ever-changing city. 
